<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07841</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROHIBITING THE USE AND INSTALLATION OF BRIGHT WHITE HEADLIGHTS OR HEADLAMPS CLASSIFIED AS HIGH INTENSITY DISCHARGE (HID) HEADLAMPS IN MOTOR VEHICLES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to reduce road accidents and improve the overall safety and convenience of our motorists by banning the use or installation of high intensity discharge “xenon headlights/headlamps”; Imposes a fine of one hundred thousand (P100,000.00) for every sale of a motor vehicle fitted with such prohibited headlamps and a fine of ten thousand pesos (P10,000.00) for every violation by the owner and driver of a motor vehicle.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Anti-High Intensity Discharge Headlamps Act”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ALEJANO, GARY C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-05-31</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Del Mar (000 2018-08-01)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON TRANSPORTATION ON 2018-07-30</td></tr></table>